Description: The goal of amethyst is to provide user-friendly tools for exploration, visualization, and analysis of single-cell methylation sequencing data. It is intended to be an interactive extension of initial processing steps described here: https://github.com/adeylab/sciMETv2.
Imports: caret, cowplot, data.table, dplyr, FNN, furrr, future, future.apply, GenomicRanges, ggplot2, grDevices, gridExtra, igraph, IRanges, irlba, leiden, Matrix, mgcv, methods, plotly, plyr, purrr, randomForest, RANN, rhdf5, rlang, Rmagic, Rphenograph, rtracklayer, Rtsne, scales, stats, stringr, tibble, tidyr, umap, utils
